in%20Fort%20Worth%2C%20Tex%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a988d643bb77284b9e406f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpal%20Lee%2C%20known%20as%20the%20'Grandmother%20of%20Juneteenth%2C'%20recently%20regained%20possession%20of%20land%20her%20family%20was%20driven%20away%20from%20more%20than%20eight%20decades%20ago.%3Cp%3ELM%20Otero%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOpal%20Lee%20is%20a%2097-year-old%20former%20teacher%20who%20advocated%20to%20make%20Juneteenth%20a%20national%20holiday.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20Lee%20was%2012%20years%20old%2C%20her%20family%20was%20driven%20off%20their%20land.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMore%20than%2080%20years%20later%2C%20she%20regained%20the%20land%20her%20family%20lost.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20an%20as-told-to%20essay%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Opal%20Lee%2C%20a%2097-year-old%20activist%20and%20former%20teacher%20who%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideo-biden-kneels-greet-94-year-old-juneteenth-activist-opal-lee-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eadvocated%20to%20make%20Juneteenth%20a%20national%20holiday%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20The%20essay%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20describe%20my%20childhood%20as%20ideal.%20I%20was%20born%20in%20Marshall%2C%20Texas%2C%20surrounded%20by%20friends%20and%20neighbors.%20We%20were%20like%20a%20great%2C%20big%20family.%20If%20I%20did%20something%20wrong%2C%20I%20was%20chastised%20before%20I%20got%20home.%20And%20when%20I%20got%20home%2C%20my%20mom%20already%20knew%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20have%20the%20slightest%20idea%20about%20white%20folks%20because%20our%20community%20was%20all%20Black.%20The%20only%20white%20people%20I%20saw%20growing%20up%20were%20a%20salesman%20who%20sold%20housewares%20and%20clothing%20from%20his%20car%20and%20a%20family%20that%20ran%20a%20grocery%20store%20at%20the%20end%20of%20our%20street.%20So%20I%20had%20no%20animosity.%20I%20was%20a%20sheltered%20child.%20I%20didn't%20know%20white%20people%20until%20we%20got%20to%20Fort%20Worth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20moved%20to%20Fort%20Worth%20when%20I%20was%2010%20years%20old.%20The%20elementary%20school%20I%20attended%20was%20on%20a%20city%20dump%2C%20like%20many%20other%20buildings%20they%20had%20for%20Black%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20family%20bought%20a%20home%20in%20a%20neighborhood%20where%20we%20weren't%20wanted%2C%20but%20we%20didn't%20know%20that.%20On%20June%2019%2C%201939%2C%20around%20500%20people%20started%20gathering%20across%20the%20street.%20The%20police%20were%20there%2C%20too.%20We'd%20only%20been%20in%20the%20house%20about%20four%20or%20five%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20sent%20us%20to%20our%20neighbors%2C%20and%20they%20left%20under%20the%20cover%20of%20darkness.%20Those%20people%20tore%20that%20place%20asunder.%20They%20did%20despicable%20things.%20They%20dragged%20the%20furniture%20out%20and%20burned%20it.%20It%20was%20horrible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20never%2C%20ever%20discussed%20what%20happened%20that%20night%20with%20us%2C%20not%20one%20time.%20It%20became%20buried%20in%20my%20psyche.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Opal%20Lee%20stands%20in%20front%20of%20her%20window%20at%20her%20home%20in%20Fort%20Worth%2C%20Texas%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65aae1b46979d73718250097%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22661%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELee%20gained%20national%20attention%20when%20she%20started%20the%20Opal's%20Walk%20Campaign%20to%20make%20Juneteenth%20a%20national%20holiday.%20It's%20now%20an%20annual%20event%20with%20thousands%20of%20people.%3Cp%3ELM%20Otero%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3ERegaining%20our%20land%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20to%20Fort%20Worth's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fold-school-vintage-classroom-photos-evolution-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20Black%20high%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20graduated%20when%20I%20was%2016%20years%20old.%20I%20got%20married%20and%20had%20four%20children%20before%20I%20realized%20I%20would%20be%20raising%20my%20husband%20too.%20I%20got%20divorced%20after%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20back%20home%20to%20Marshall%20and%20went%20to%20Wiley%20College.%20I%20worked%20I%20don't%20know%20how%20many%20jobs%20to%20pay%20for%20college%20and%20to%20support%20my%20kids.%20I%20finished%20college%20in%20three%20and%20a%20half%20years%20because%20I%20couldn't%20stay%20for%20four%2C%20and%20became%20a%20teacher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%20years%20later%2C%20a%20friend%20of%20mine%20who%20works%20at%20the%20Star-Telegram%2C%20a%20local%20newspaper%20in%20Fort%20Worth%2C%20mentioned%20the%20land%20my%20family%20had%20bought%20all%20those%20years%20ago.%20I%20looked%20it%20up%20and%20saw%20the%20land%20was%20vacant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELo%20and%20behold%2C%20I%20saw%20that%20Habitat%20for%20Humanity%20owned%20it.%20I%20had%20once%20been%20on%20Habitat's%20board%2C%20so%20I%20called%20up%20Gage%20Yager%2C%20the%20CEO%2C%20and%20asked%20him%20to%20sell%20the%20lot%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20no%2C%20they%20weren't%20going%20to%20sell%20it%20to%20me%2C%20because%20they%20were%20going%20to%20give%20it%20to%20me.%20I%20was%20so%20overwhelmed.%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BNow%20I'm%20going%20to%20build%20a%20house%20on%20the%20land.%26quot%3B%20Gage%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20build%20that%20house%20for%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20could%20have%20done%20a%20holy%20dance%2C%20but%20the%20kids%20say%20when%20I%20do%20that%2C%20I'm%20twerking%2C%20so%20I%20didn't%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBecoming%20a%20committee%20of%20one%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20successfully%20helped%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjuneteenth-freedom-emancipation-day-parade-pageants-galveston-celebration-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJuneteenth%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcongress-voted-to-make-juneteenth-federal-holiday-heres-why-it-took-decades-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecome%20a%20national%20holiday%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20was%20in%20hog%20heaven.%20To%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjuneteenth-federal-holiday-biden-signs-bill-employees-get-friday-off-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewatch%20the%20president%20sign%20Juneteenth%20into%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20was%20awestruck.%20I%20still%20am.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22President%20Joe%20Biden%20hands%20out%20a%20pen%20after%20signing%20the%20Juneteenth%20National%20Independence%20Day%20Act%2C%20in%20the%20East%20Room%20of%20the%20White%20House.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a9884e6979d737182475f7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22655%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpal%20Lee%20(bottom%20second%20from%20left)%20attended%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20signing%20of%20the%20Juneteenth%20National%20Independence%20Day%20Act.%3Cp%3EEvan%20Vucci%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20always%20someone%20who%20needs%20something.%20I'm%20a%20deaconess%20at%20my%20church%2C%20and%20I%20deliver%20boxes%20of%20food%20to%20people%20who%20need%20it%20twice%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20want%20people%20to%20realize%20they%20can%20make%20themselves%20a%20committee%20of%20one%20to%20change%20somebody's%20mind%2C%20because%20if%20people%20can%20be%20taught%20to%20hate%2C%20they%20can%20be%20taught%20to%20love.%20It's%20left%20up%20to%20each%20of%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20know%20people%20who%20aren't%20on%20the%20same%20page%20as%20us%2C%20and%20we%20can%20change%20their%20minds.%20We%20just%20have%20to%2