s%20only%20exacerbated%20by%20the%20attack%20on%20his%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20attempted%20escape%2C%20he%20stabs%20Deputy%20Witt%20Farr%20(Lamorne%20Morris)%20in%20the%20heart%2C%20mercilessly%20killing%20the%20dedicated%20officer.%20While%20Tillman%20believes%20he's%20escaped%20scot-free%20by%20using%20an%20old%20tunnel%20that%20leads%20into%20a%20field%2C%20he's%20surrounded%20by%20the%20FBI%2C%20and%20taken%20into%20custody.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20does%20the%20sheriff%20have%20to%20face%20the%20fact%20that%20he's%20not%20above%20the%20law%2C%20but%20he's%20told%20that%20his%20son%20Gator%20(Joe%20Keery)%20is%20the%20one%20who%20told%20the%20authorities%20about%20the%20tunnel.%20Think%20of%20it%20as%20karma%20for%20all%20the%20abuse%20that%20Gator%20has%20endured%20at%20Roy's%20hands%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20punishment%20doesn't%20stop%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone's%20favorite%20debt%20collector%2C%20Lorraine%20Lyon%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjennifer-jason-leigh-most-famous-roles-fargo-hateful-eight-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJennifer%20Jason%20Leigh%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20later%20visits%20Roy%20in%20prison.%20She%20explains%20that%20she's%20helping%20hundreds%20of%20inmates%20pay%20off%20their%20debts%20in%20exchange%20for%20making%20his%20life%20sentence%20a%20living%20hell%20as%20revenge%20for%20the%20abuse%20he%20inflicted%20on%20her%20daughter-in-law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20as%20the%20prisoners%20behind%20Roy%20start%20grinning%20menacingly%2C%20it%20doesn't%20take%20a%20genius%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20the%20former%20sheriff's%20future%20will%20look%20like%20behind%20bars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDot%20reunites%20with%20her%20family%20and%20frees%20Ole%20Munch%20of%20his%20sins%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222046%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sam%20Spruell%20as%20Ole%20Munch%20in%20the%20%26quot%3BFargo%26quot%3B%20season%20five%20finale.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65aab9cbdcdb354a98590f7f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221346%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESam%20Spruell%20as%20Ole%20Munch%20in%20the%20%26quot%3BFargo%26quot%3B%20season%20five%20finale.%3Cp%3EFX%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDot%20takes%20her%20old%20life%20back%20and%20returns%20home%20to%20her%20husband%20Wayne%20(David%20Rysdahl)%20and%20their%20daughter%2C%20Scotty%20(Sienna%20King).%20But%20jumping%20ahead%20to%20a%20year%20after%20the%20compound%20raid%2C%20she's%20at%20peace%20with%20her%20past%20and%20is%20trying%20to%20move%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20peaceful%20existence%20is%20briefly%20interrupted%20when%20Ole%20Munch%20(Sam%20Spruell)%20turns%20up%20at%20the%20Lyons'%20house%20to%20claim%20the%20debt%20he%20feels%20that%20Dot%20owes%20him.%20This%20is%20because%20their%20fight%20was%20never%20properly%20finished%20when%20he%20originally%20attempted%20to%20kidnap%20her%20for%20Roy%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%20most%20poignant%20conversation%20of%20the%20season%2C%20Dot%20invites%20Munch%20to%20make%20food%20and%20have%20a%20meal%20with%20her%20family%2C%20effectively%20forgiving%20him%20for%20his%20violent%20nature.%20As%20they%20talk%2C%20Munch%20explains%20his%20history%20as%20a%20sin-eater%20and%20implies%20that%20the%20nature%20of%20taking%20on%20other%20people's%20sins%20and%20absorbing%20their%20debt%20is%20neverending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Dot%20suggests%20that%20it%20only%20takes%20one%20person%20to%20break%20the%20cycle%2C%20much%20like%20she%20helped%20break%20the%20cycle%20of%20abuse%20that%20she%20was%20trapped%20in%20with%20Roy.%20By%20eating%20a%20meal%20with%20the%20Lyon%20family%2C%20Munch%20can%20finally%20feel%20warmth%2C%20and%20happiness%2C%20rather%20than%20pain%20and%20misery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESo%2C%20does%20'Fargo'%20season%205%20connect%20to%20previous%20seasons%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width