20Nazi%20society%20were%20based%20upon%20whom%20you%20have%20married.%20The%20Law%20for%20the%20Protection%20of%20German%20Blood%20and%20German%20Honour%20of%201935%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jewishvirtuallibrary.org%2Flaw-for-the-protection-of-german-blood-and-german-honor%5C%22%3Eprohibited%3C%2Fa%3E%20marriages%20between%20Aryans%20and%20Jews%20and%20it%20also%20required%20to%20establish%20one%E2%80%99s%20racial%20purity%20before%20a%20marriage%20could%20be%20solemnised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20core%20of%20such%20laws%20prohibiting%20inter-community%20marriages%20is%20economic%20exploitation%20and%20controlling%20women%E2%80%99s%20sexual%20autonomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FSex-Love-Race-Crossing-Boundaries%2Fdp%2F0814735568%5C%22%3ESex%2C%20Love%2C%20Race%3A%20Crossing%20Boundaries%20in%20North%20American%20History%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3EMartha%20Hodes%20depicts%20that%20with%20these%20laws%2C%20the%20colonists%20intended%20to%20ensure%20continued%20exploitation%20of%20Africans%20and%20shunned%20their%20chances%20to%20rise%20up%20in%20the%20social%20hierarchy.%20This%20was%20also%20reinforced%20with%20the%20%E2%80%98one%20drop%20rule%E2%80%99%2C%20wherein%20if%20a%20person%20was%20known%20to%20have%201%25%20of%20African%20blood%20in%20his%20veins%2C%20he%20ceased%20to%20be%20a%20white%20man.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20England%2C%20the%20legislation%20that%20established%20the%20State%E2%80%99s%20control%20over%20marriage%2C%20known%20as%20the%20Marriage%20Act%20of%201753%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Flaw-and-history-review%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fcontrol-over-marriage-in-england-and-wales-17531823-the-clandestine-marriages-act-of-1753-in-context%2F53ACCF95BFF38504BF9A5A5E31C75B76%5C%22%3Eaimed%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20to%20do%20away%20with%20the%20lack%20of%20clarity%20and%20uncertainty%20regarding%20property%20for%20the%20landed%20elites.%20The%20Act%20also%20restrained%20clandestine%20marriages%20amongst%20the%20children.%20All%20this%20was%20done%20in%20the%20name%20of%20moral%20paternalism%20and%20to%20protect%20children%20from%20moral%20turpitude.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fhindu-rashtra-love-faith-consent%5C%22%3ELove%2C%20Faith%20and%20Consent%20in%20a%20Hindu%20Rashtra%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMoral%20paternalism%20by%20the%20State%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustifying%20moral%20paternalism%2C%20professor%20Gerald%20Dworkin%20argues%20that%20the%20State%20engages%20in%20regulating%20social%20institutions%2C%20such%20as%20marriage%2C%20for%20an%20individual%E2%80%99s%20own%20moral%20good.%20However%2C%20the%20notions%20of%20morality%20are%20different%20for%20each%20person%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20by%20adopting%20the%20role%20of%20a%20parent%2C%20the%20State%20forces%20an%20individual%20to%20act%20according%20to%20the%20majoritarian%20notion%20of%20morality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20major%20criticisms%20of%20this%20theory%20is%20propounded%20by%20Gerald%E2%80%99s%20counterpart%2C%20professor%20Ronald%20Dworkin%2C%20who%20asks%20a%20pertinent%20question%3A%20what%20if%20the%20person%20being%20forced%20to%20live%20a%20certain%20way%20post%20the%20paternalistic%20intervention%20is%20not%20happy%20and%20he%20regrets%20this%20intervention%3F%20This%20criticism%20has%20been%20raised%20in%20the%20Indian%20context%20as%20well%2C%20wherein%20attempts%20at%20making%20parental%20consent%20necessary%20in%20marriages%20has%20been%20seen%20as%20restricting%20an%20individual%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIs%20it%20right%20to%20interfere%20in%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20life%20just%20because%20we%20think%20that%20it%20will%20improve%20the%20person%E2%80%99s%20moral%20state%2C%20despite%20such%20an%20act%20being%20against%20his%20happiness%3F%20Even%20Ten%20Chin%20Liew%2C%20in%20his%20very%20definition%20of%20moral%20paternalism%2C%20underlies%20a%20presumption%20of%20absence%20of%20full%20and%20free%20consent%20of%20the%20individual.%20Since%2C%20matrimonial%20alliances%20are%20entered%20by%20the%20full%20and%20free%20consent%20of%20the%20partners%2C%20moral%20paternalism%20by%20the%20State%20should%20have%20no%20role%20in%20governing%20these%20alliances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20jurist%2C%20C.%20Edwin%20Harris%2C%20argues%20that%20if%20a%20person%20rationally%20takes%20a%20decision%2C%20then%20he%20cannot%20be%20refrained%20from%20committing%20such%20an%20act%20in%20the%20name%20of%20paternalism.%20Thus%2C%20the%20justification%20by%20the%20State%20that%20it%20is%20acting%20as%20a%20guardian%20of%20the%20moral%20fabric%20of%20the%20society%20fails%2C%20because%20the%20individual%20has%20full%20right%20to%20take%20a%20decision%20governing%20his%20personal%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERight%20to%20marry%20a%20person%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20choice%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20pertinent%20aspect%20is%20that%20in%202014%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20while%20taking%20suo%20moto%20cognisance%20of%20a%20woman%20being%20gang-raped%20because%20she%20married%20a%20person%20from%20a%20different%20community%2C%20observed%20that%20the%20right%20of%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20choice%20to%20marry%20whom%20she%20pleases%20in%20an%20inherent%20part%20of%20individual%20dignity%20and%20intrinsic%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F15240%2F1%2Fconstitution_of_india.pdf%5C%22%3EArticle%2021%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Law%20Commission%20of%20India%20in%20its%20242nd%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdnbbsr.s3waas.gov.in%2Fs3ca0daec69b5adc880fb464895726dbdf%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F2022081053-3.pdf%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20%E2%80%98Prevention%20of%20Interference%20with%20the%20Freedom%20of%20Matrimonial%20Alliances%20(in%20the%20name%20of%20Honour%20and%20Tradition)%3A%20A%20Suggested%20Legal%20Framework%E2%80%99%20said%20that%20non-interference%20of%20any%20third%20party%2C%20including%20parents%2C%20other%20family%20members%20and%20vigilante%20groups%2C%20and%20respecting%20individual%20preferences%20in%20matters%20of%20matrimonial%20alliances%2C%20are%20hallmarks%20of%20a%20progressive%20society.%20These%20aspects%20symbolise%20progression%20from%20political%20democracy%20towards%20the%20attainment%20of%20social%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2010%2F18233%2F18233_2010_Judgement_27-Mar-2018.pdf%5C%22%3EShakti%20Vahini%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20court%20observed%20that%20when%20two%20adults%20consensually%20choose%20each%20other%20as%20life%20partners%2C%20it%20is%20a%20manifestation%20of%20their%20choice%20which%20is%20recognised%20under%20Articles%2019%20and%2021%20of%20the%20constitution.%20Such%20a%20right%20has%20the%20sanction%20of%20constitutional%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20in%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1364215%2F%5C%22%3ELata%20Singh%20v.%20State%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20top%20court%20held%20that%20a%20person%20who%20has%20attained%20the%20age%20of%20marriage%20has%20a%20right%20to%20decide%20whom%20does%20he%2Fshe%20want%20to%20marry%20and%20no%20statute%20can%20curtail%20the%20exercise%20of%20such%20right.%20Furthermore%2C%20in%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2017%2F19702%2F19702_2017_Judgement_08-Mar-2018.pdf%5C%22%3EShafin%20Jahan%20v.%20Asokan%20K.M%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20court%20felt%20that%20it%20is%20the%20State%E2%80%99s%20duty%20to%20preserve%20the%20individual%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20choose%20a%20partner%20for%20himself%20freely%20without%20any%20coercion%20whatsoever.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fthe-interface-of-love-and-jihad-is-a-false-indian-articulation%5C%22%3EThe%20Interface%20of%20%E2%80%98Love%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Jihad%E2%80%99%20Is%20a%20False%20Indian%20Articulation%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20myth%20around%20divorces%20in%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20misplaced%20assumption%20is%20that%20the%20traditional%20arranged%20marriage%20system%20leads%20to%20stability%20in%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freepressjournal.in%2Fviral%2Fwith-1-divorce-rate-india-tops-in-maintaining-relationships-check-full-list-to-know-where-most-divorces-happen%5C%22%3Elow%20divorce%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20is%20not%20necessarily%20a%20healthy%20indicator%20but%20a%20privilege%20which%20most%20of%20the%20Indian%20women%20are%20deprived%20of%20due%20to%20the%20stigma%20around%20divorce%20and%20social%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20National%20Family%20Health%20Survey%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20divorce%20cases%20are%20related%20to%20instances%20of%20abuse.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.mohfw.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FNFHS-5_Phase-II_0.pdf%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20highlighted%20that%20nearly%2030%25%20of%20married%20women%20are%20victims%20of%20domestic%20abuse.%20However%2C%20as%20many%20as%2077%25%20of%20the%20victims%20choose%20not%20to%20speak%20up%20against%20abuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20reason%20behind%20low%20divorce%20rates%20is%20the%20prevalence%20of%20instances%20where%20husbands%20abandon%20their%20wives%20without%20formally%20filing%20for%20divorce%20to%20evade%20legal%20responsibilities.%C2%A0Men%20often%20enjoy%20the%20privilege%20of%20being%20able%20to%20abandon%20their%20spouses%20without%20formally%20filing%20for%20divorce%2C%20while%20women%20in%20conservative%20Indian%20families%20are%20often%20raised%20to%20internalize%20the%20expectation%20of%20unconditional%20compromise%2C%20resulting%20in%20shattered%20self-esteem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2F873-dr-nirmal-singh-panesar-v-paramjit-kaur-panesar-ajinder-10-oct-2023-507659.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDr%20Nirmal%20Singh%20Panesar%20v.%20Mrs.%20Paramjit%20Kaur%20Panesar%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20recognised%20%E2%80%9Cirretrievable%20breakdown%20of%20marriage%E2%80%9D%20as%20a%20valid%20ground%20to%20seek%20divorce%20and%20has%20waived%20the%20six-month%20waiting%20period.%20This%20has%20provided%20some%20hope%20to%20couples%20trapped%20in%20unhealthy%20marital%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrioritising%20forced%20stability%20in%20the%20marriage%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20normalising%20and%20neglecting%20hopeless%20compromise%2C%20domestic%20abuse%2C%20marital%20rape%20and%20abandonment%20would%20prove%20to%20be%20fatal%20for%20gender%20equality%20in%20India.%20The%20State%E2%80%99s%20act%20of%20curbing%20consent%20in%20case%20of%20marriage%20snatches%20away%20a%20women%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20annul%20such%20a%20marriage%2C%20thereby%2C%20forcing%20them%20into%20unwanted%20relationships%2C%20leading%20to%20their%20institutional%20exploitation%20by%20the%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705753819000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F19120045%2FA_ritual_at_marriage_ceremony.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fissues-around-state-intervention-parental-consent-in-marriages-and-bans-on-live-in-relationships%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20justification%20by%20the%20State%20that%20it%20is%20acting%20as%20a%20guardian%20of%20the%20moral%20fabric%20of%20the%20society%20fails%2C%20because%20the%20individual%20has%20full%20right%20to%20take%20a%20decision%20governing%20his%20personal%20life.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2