ookings%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20hotel%20manager%20Hamid%20Masoodi.%20%26quot%3BThose%20who%20come%20despite%20no%20snow%20are%20also%20disappointed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESki%20lifts%20are%20closed%2C%20rental%20shops%20are%20shut%20and%20a%20newly%20constructed%20ice%20rink%20is%20a%20pool%20of%20dank%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20current%20dry%20spell%20is%20an%20extreme%20weather%20event%20--%20which%20are%20predicted%20to%20become%20more%20intense%20and%20frequent%20in%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20climate%20scientist%20Shakil%20Romshoo%2C%20from%20Kashmir's%20Islamic%20University%20of%20Science%20and%20Technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3ERising%20temperatures%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20an%20insurgency%20seeking%20independence%20or%20a%20merger%20with%20Pakistan%20--%20and%20military%20operations%20to%20crush%20that%20movement%20--%20has%20seen%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20civilians%2C%20soldiers%20and%20rebels%20killed%20in%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rebellion%20has%20lost%20much%20of%20its%20former%20strength%2C%20and%20India%20has%20been%20heavily%20promoting%20domestic%20tourism%20in%20the%20region%2C%20home%20to%20spectacular%20mountain%20scenery%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20Gulmarg%2C%20hotel%20bookings%20have%20plunged%20by%20as%20much%20as%20three-quarters%2C%20tourism%20professionals%20say%2C%20as%20hundreds%20of%20guides%20and%20scooter%20drivers%20sit%20waiting%20in%20the%20sunshine%2C%20praying%20for%20snow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20foreigners%20who%20mainly%20come%20for%20skiing%20on%20the%20deep%20powder%20slopes%20have%20cancelled%2C%26quot%3B%20Bakshi%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20lost%20about%2070%20percent%20of%20bookings%20so%20far.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerched%20at%208%2C694%20feet%2C%20the%20Himalayan%20resort%20is%20also%20home%20to%20the%20Indian%20army's%20High%20Altitude%20Warfare%20School%2C%20located%20close%20to%20the%20highly%20militarised%20Line%20of%20Control%2C%20the%20de%20facto%20border%20that%20divides%20contested%20Kashmir%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKashmir%20has%20recorded%20little%20rain%2C%20and%20temperatures%20are%20about%20six%20degrees%20Celsius%20(42.4%20degrees%20Fahrenheit)%20higher%20than%20normal%20since%20autumn%20last%20year%2C%20according%20to%20meteorology%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20precipitation%20across%20Kashmir%20was%20down%2080%20percent%20from%20past%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGulmarg%20received%20a%20few%20snow%20showers%2C%20but%20that%20soon%20melted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMinistry%20of%20Earth%20Sciences%20said%20in%20a%202020%20report%20they%20expected%20the%20Himalayas%20and%20Kashmir%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bparticularly%20subject%26quot%3B%20to%20warming%20temperatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20the%20UN's%20World%20Meteorological%20Organization%20said%20the%202023%20annual%20average%20global%20temperature%20was%201.45%20degrees%20Celsius%20above%20pre-industrial%20levels%20(1850-1900)%20--%20the%20warmest%20year%20on%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20nine%20hottest%20individual%20years%20on%20record%20were%20the%20last%20nine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Kashmir%2C%20the%20impact%20is%20clear.%20Gulmarg's%20bowl-shaped%20landscape%2C%20beloved%20by%20tourists%20for%20the%20snow%20in%20winter%20and%20meadows%20of%20flowers%20in%20spring%2C%20is%20brown%20and%20bleak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E'Prolonged%20dry%20spells'%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20warn%20rising%20global%20temperatures%20are%20unleashing%20a%20cascade%20of%20extreme%20weather%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20skiing%20industry%2C%20many%20in%20the%20ecologically%20fragile%20region%20are%20worried%20about%20impending%20water%20shortages%20that%20would%20have%20a%20dire%20potential%20impact%20on%20agriculture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERomshoo%2C%20the%20climate%20scientist%2C%20said%20research%20indicates%20Kashmir%20%26q